public StringName getName()
The name attribute is used to store a single string token that represents a unique name for an object. A name should be composed of characters in the range, [a-z] [A-Z] [0-9]. No whitespace characters are allowed. All names must start with a character.

getBlockWhenLocked

public java.lang.Boolean getBlockWhenLocked()
This flag indicates whether or not an Action will be blocked from proceeding if there is a DAF lock on the object against which the action is performed. The default is to block all incoming actions against a locked object. By setting this flag to false, you can allow an action to proceed.

getIsGetAction

public java.lang.Boolean getIsGetAction()
This flag indicates if an Action is merely a data retrieval (get) Action. Actions that are flagged with this attribute set to true will be executable even when the server is in a read-only mode because they don't actually alter data. One example of this is the getAllowedOperations() action on the SecurityBranch.
